translated: Lindblom, Nils Solve Isak Natanael, clergyman, Laholm, born on November 26, 1895 in Fjelkestad, Kristianstad. Son of assistant priest Nathanael L. and Kaura Been. Married on May 25 to Märta Kleberg. - Graduated from high school in 1914, Bachelor of Theology.. passed practical theology exam and ordained as a priest in 1921. Assistant priest in Bro and Brastad from 1926, appointed as vicar in Laholm in 1940. Chairman of the church council since 1940, member of the school board since the same year, representative and vice chairman of the County Library Board since 1942. Former chairman of the church assembly, the Children's Welfare Committee, representing the North Bohuslän district of the People's Friends of Primary Schools. Former vice chairman of the Brastad YRC district, memorial speaker at the clergy meeting in Gothenburg in 1945, appointed for the same task until 1951. Writings: contributions as a collaborator in newspapers and magazines.
